' @id(SEQ-CANVAS-FISHEYE)
' @ref(USE-FISHEYE-FOCUS)
' @desc(SEQ-CANVAS-FISHEYE, "Per-frame canvas flow in code: base scale from scroll zoom + drag pan, then CanvasView::fisheye_mesh warps the rendered texture around the canvas centre before egui paints it; no toolbar zoom buttons exist.")
' Current-side flow derived from MddViewer::update / CanvasView in
' crates/mdd-viewer/src/lib.rs.
title Focus a diagram region with the center fisheye (current)

actor "Developer" as Dev <<added>>
participant "MddViewer\n(eframe::App)" as Viewer
participant "CanvasView\n(base_zoom, pan, fisheye_*)" as CV
participant "DiagramPage\n(rasterized texture)" as Tex
participant "egui painter" as Painter

Dev -> Viewer : scroll wheel over canvas (resp.hovered)
Viewer -> CV : base_zoom *= factor at cursor; pan adjusted
Dev -> Viewer : drag canvas (resp.dragged)
Viewer -> CV : pan += drag_delta
note right of CV
  No Reset / Zoom +/- buttons (svg_toolbar shows
  only the PAGE selector + a hint). Focal is the
  canvas-rect centre (CanvasView::focal); fisheye_radius
  is set each frame to the farthest-corner distance so
  corners stay fixed (OCL-FISHEYE-FOCAL-CENTER).
end note

loop each painted frame
  Viewer -> Tex : rebuild texture at base_zoom if needed
  Viewer -> CV : fisheye_mesh(tex, draw_rect, focal)
  CV -> CV : warp() each grid vertex (56x56) radially
  note right of CV
    warp: nd = dist/radius; f = (1-s)*nd + s*sin(nd*PI/2);
    pos = focal + v * (radius * f / d). Centre magnifies,
    edges compress. UVs unchanged so text stays crisp.
  end note
  CV --> Viewer : textured Mesh
  Viewer -> Painter : painter.add(Shape::mesh(mesh)) clipped to canvas
  Painter --> Dev : centre bulges, edges curve away
end
@enduml
